.# TradeTrackr — V1 Launch Roadmap

> **Goal**: Ship a production-ready trading journal that is stable, beautiful, and powerful enough to replace spreadsheets and compete with TradeZella.
> **Rule**: Each chunk should be completable in 1–2 focused sessions. Tick items as you go.

---

## ✅ PHASE 0 — Foundation (Done)

- [x] Core dashboard with equity curve, drawdown gauge, streak tracker
- [x] Analytics page with "Cost of Mistakes" module
- [x] Light/Dark theme system with toggle
- [x] Trade log (add, view, tag, annotate trades)
- [x] Forex pips/lots tracking
- [x] Global Error Boundaries on dash;board
- [x] Mobile slide-out navigation drawer
- [x] TypeScript strict mode cleanup (tradeMetrics, aiService)
- [x] Economic Calendar API (mock data fallback)
- [x] Supabase auth (login / signup / session handling)

---

## ✅ PHASE 1 — Critical Bug Fixes (Done)

- [x] **1.1** Duplicate trade on scroll — `if (isSubmitting) return` guard in `EnhancedTradeForm`
- [x] **1.2** Input not saving — confirmed `handleChange` uses correct functional state update pattern
- [x] **1.3** `trade.pips is null` crash — added `?? 0` guard in `TradeDetail.tsx`
- [x] **1.4** Light mode visual audit — fixed card/panel classes in dashboard, analytics, settings
- [x] **1.5** Settings page theme toggle — confirmed `useTheme` + `setTheme` wired to Sun/Moon/Monitor buttons
- [x] **1.6** Auth redirect loop — removed all `window.location.href`; replaced with `router.push`; fixed `signOut` AuthSessionMissingError
- [x] **1.7** Calendar loading bug — fixed infinite loading state when user is unauthenticated
- [x] **1.8** Calendar month offset bug — fixed `getFirstDayOfMonth` to use Monday-start index; hidden empty-cell day numbers

---

## ✅ PHASE 2 — UX & Design Polish (Done)

- [x] **2.1 Skeleton Loaders** — `SkeletonLoader.tsx` with `DashboardSkeleton`, `TradesSkeleton`, `AnalyticsSkeleton`, `CalendarSkeleton` in `src/components/ui/`
- [x] **2.2 Toast Notifications** — `ToastProvider.tsx` wired up; success/error toasts for trade save, delete, etc.
- [x] **2.3 Empty States** — `EmptyState.tsx` component used on Analytics, Calendar, and Trades pages
- [x] **2.4 Micro-animations** — `framer-motion` entry animations on all dashboard cards; liquid glass card hover lifts
- [x] **2.5 Liquid Glass Theme** — Full liquid surface theme applied globally via `globals.css`; affects all cards, inputs, buttons across dashboard, analytics, trades, calendar, settings, signup/login pages
- [x] **2.6 Mobile Navigation** — Slide-out drawer; responsive layouts audited
- [x] **2.7 Favicon & Branding** — Custom `favicon.ico` + `icon.png` present; correct `<title>` tags on all pages
- [x] **2.8 404 & Error Pages** — `not-found.tsx` (2.8KB) and `error.tsx` (3.6KB) match app design language
- [x] **2.9 Landing Page** — Full marketing landing page at `/` with hero, features grid, stats bar, "How it works", CTA section, footer

---

## ✅ PHASE 3 — Core Feature Completions (Done)

- [x] **3.1 Trade Detail Page (`/trades/[id]`)** — Full single-trade view: notes, tags, pips, P&L, entry screenshot slot, AI analysis, edit page at `/trades/[id]/edit`
- [x] **3.2 Calendar Page** — Wired to actual trade data; clicking a day shows day's trades in sidebar; week & month view modes; P&L heat coloring
- [x] **3.3 Profile Page** — Shows user info (email, joined date, account balance, total trades); update display name
- [x] **3.4 Settings — General Tab** — Default currency, starting balance, timezone, date format; saves & reads from Supabase
- [x] **3.5 Settings — Notifications Tab** — Toggle in-app notifications; saved to user preferences
- [x] **3.6 Welcome / Onboarding Flow** — `welcome/page.tsx` (11KB) — 3-step onboarding wizard shown once on first login
- [x] **3.7 "New Trade" Form Validation** — Required field validation, invalid price format warnings; `isSubmitting` guard
- [x] **3.8 Bulk Delete Trades** — Checkbox selection + bulk delete on the trades list page

---

## ✅ PHASE 4 — Prop Firm Feature Set (Done)

- [x] **4.1 Prop Firm Presets Database** — `src/lib/propFirms.ts` (15KB): 10 firms × multiple tiers — FTMO, E8, FundedNext, The5%ers, Apex, Topstep, Goat Funded, Funding Pips, MyFundedFX, True Forex Funds — with daily loss, total loss, profit target, trailing drawdown, consistency rules
- [x] **4.2 Firm Selector UI in Settings** — Dropdown in Settings → "Account" tab; stores selected firm config in Supabase
- [x] **4.3 Challenge Dashboard Widget** — `ChallengeDashboardWidget.tsx` (9KB): profit progress bar, daily drawdown danger meter, days remaining countdown, violation indicator
- [x] **4.4 Real-time Violation Alerts** — Red alert banner when today's P&L drops below firm's daily loss limit
- [x] **4.5 `computeChallengeStatus` helper** — Full violation detection, progress calculation, drawdown % tracking

---

## ✅ PHASE 6 — Performance & Scalability (Done)

> *Phase 5 (MT5 Import) is intentionally skipped to Phase 7 — see below.*

- [x] **6.1 Trades List Virtualization** — Server-side pagination prevents loading all trades at once; effective virtualization at DB layer
- [x] **6.2 Server-Side Pagination** — `getPagedTrades()` in `tradingApi.ts` uses Supabase `.range()` + `count: 'exact'`; filters pushed to DB (symbol, type, date, search, sort)
- [x] **6.3 Memoize Heavy Calculations** — Analytics page: all 9 chart datasets in single `useMemo`; Trades page: `uniqueSymbols`, `reviewQueue`, `topMistakeCost` memoized
- [x] **6.4 Image Optimization** — `compressImage()` in `supabaseClient.ts`: resize to 1920px max + JPEG@85% before upload (~10× size reduction); `next.config.js` uses `remotePatterns` + AVIF/WebP format support + 7-day TTL
- [x] **6.5 Bundle Splitting** — All 10 analytics chart components use `next/dynamic`; Webpack `splitChunks` cache groups for `recharts`, `framer-motion`, `@tremor` in `next.config.js`; `@next/bundle-analyzer` added (run `npm run analyze`)

---

## ✅ PHASE 5 — Data Import (Done)

> Removes the #1 reason people don't journal: "it's too much work to enter trades manually."

- [x] **5.1 MT5 HTML Report Parser** — Regex-based HTML parser in `importParsers.ts`: handles UTF-16 encoding, positions table, deals table pairing, symbol/type/time/lots/price/profit/commission/swap extraction
- [x] **5.2 Drag-and-Drop Import UI** — `/import` page with drag-drop zone, format tabs (MT5/CSV), preview table with checkboxes, summary bar, import button
- [x] **5.3 Duplicate Detection** — Key = `symbol + entry_time + lots`; shows "X duplicates skipped" after import
- [x] **5.4 CSV Import (Generic)** — Configurable column mapping with presets for cTrader and ThinkorSwim; auto-detects delimiter
- [x] **5.5 Import History** — Full import history table with file name, source, trades imported, duplicates skipped, date, and delete capability

---

## 🔐 PHASE 7 — Security & Database (Next Priority)

> Non-negotiable before going public.

- [ ] **7.1 Supabase RLS Audit** — Verify ALL tables have Row Level Security enabled; users must only read/write their own data
- [ ] **7.2 API Key Security** — No API keys exposed client-side (OpenAI); all external calls through Next.js API routes
- [ ] **7.3 Input Sanitization** — Sanitize all user text inputs (notes, tags) before saving to prevent XSS
- [ ] **7.4 Rate Limiting** — Rate limiting on API routes (especially AI endpoints) to prevent abuse
- [ ] **7.5 Environment Variables Audit** — Create `.env.example` documenting all required env vars; ensure `.env.local` is in `.gitignore`

---

## 🚀 PHASE 8 — Deployment & Launch

> The final steps to go live.

- [ ] **8.1 Domain & Hosting** — Choose host (Vercel recommended for Next.js); purchase domain (e.g., tradetrackr.io)
- [ ] **8.2 Production Supabase Project** — Separate Supabase project for production (don't use dev DB for real users)
- [ ] **8.3 Environment Variables in Vercel** — Add all env vars to Vercel dashboard; test they resolve correctly in production build
- [ ] **8.4 SEO Pass** — Add `<meta>` description, OpenGraph image, and Twitter card to the landing page *(hero, features, CTA already built — just needs meta tags)*
- [ ] **8.5 Error Monitoring** — Integrate **Sentry** (free tier) for production error tracking
- [ ] **8.6 Analytics** — Add **Vercel Analytics** or **Plausible** to track page views (privacy-first)
- [ ] **8.7 CI/CD Pipeline** — GitHub Actions: run `tsc` + `next build` on every PR; block merges on failure
- [ ] **8.8 Beta Tester Feedback** — Add "Send Feedback" button (Tally/Formbricks) visible on every page
- [ ] **8.9 Production Smoke Test** — Before announcing: new account signup → log 5 trades → verify analytics → test mobile → test light/dark mode → test prop firm widget

---

## 🔭 POST-V1 ROADMAP (Don't Build Now)

> Ideas for V2 after the first users are in.

- [ ] **TradingView Chrome Extension** — Silent sync + auto-video replay of every execution
- [ ] **News Event Flagging** — Overlay FOMC, CPI, NFP events on the trade timeline; flag "News Exposure" trades
- [ ] **Risk-of-Ruin Simulator** — Monte Carlo simulation based on current win rate and R:R
- [ ] **Position Size Calculator** — In-form tool: enter risk % + SL pips → get lot size
- [ ] **Backtesting Log** — Compare "planned" vs "executed" trades for discipline measurement
- [ ] **Mobile App (React Native)** — iOS/Android version with push notifications for drawdown alerts
- [ ] **Team / Prop Firm Admin View** — Firms can monitor all their funded traders' journals in one view
- [ ] **Trades Columns Config** — Let users show/hide columns (Pips, Lots, R:R, Tags) and remember preference

